            <title>[CAMEL-12787] Accept header is not respected anymore in CXFRS consumer when POST</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-12787</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Given the camel route as a cxfrs server (test case is here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/xldai/test/tree/master/cxfrs&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/xldai/test/tree/master/cxfrs&lt;/a&gt;), Running the Route and send POST request from curl with &quot;Accept: application/json&quot;, but the cxfrs server will always return  application/xml as Response.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note this issue only happening on POST method, for GET, the Accept header is respected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No this kind of issue on Camel 2.20.x, Camel 2.21.0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
